Quote: The waka huia was a sacred box, and was used for carrying to remote parts of the islands the feathers of the huia - a rare bird, which was found only in two ranges of mountains in the North Island, and of which the feathers were sacred and only permitted to be worn by rangatiras (chiefs) and people of gentle blood.
